<title>HONG KONG: Shaw Brothers interim net down 86.81 pct.</title>
<headline>Shaw Brothers interim net down 86.81 pct.</headline>
<dateline>HONG KONG 1996-12-10</dateline>
<text>
<p>Six months ended September 30</p>
<p>(in million HK$ unless stated)</p>
<p>    Shr (H.K. cents)	   56.0	  vs  428.0</p>
<p>    Dividend (H.K. cents)    5.0	   vs  5.0</p>
<p>    Exceptional items	  164.42 gain vs  1,621.63 gain</p>
<p>    Net			    224.96	vs  1,705.31</p>
<p>    Turnover		     38.65	 vs  72.88 (see note)</p>
<p>    Company name		 Shaw Brothers (Hong Kong) Ltd</p>
<p>    Books close		  January 4-13, 1997</p>
<p>    Dividend payable	   January 14, 1997</p>
<p>NOTE - Film producer and distributor Shaw Brothers also engages in property development and investment.</p>
<p>Comparative turnover has been re-stated to include interest income to be consistent with the revenue recognition policy adopted for the period.</p>
<p>Net is after an exceptional item of discontinued operations gain on disposal of interest in an associated company.</p>
<p>-- Hong Kong Newsroom (852) 2843 6368</p>
